	<ol id="questionList">
	
	<li>Which of the following openings are the most appropriate for this letter?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t1">I am writing to apply for the position of part-time bookshop assistant as advertised in The Post on Monday, 12th December.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t2">I'm writing about your ad for a shop assistant.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t3">I read with interest your advertisement in The Post on Monday, 12th December and I would like to apply for the position of part-time bookshop assistant.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t4">I saw your job in the paper and I want to apply.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t5">I've always wanted a job in a shop so when I saw your advert in the paper on Monday, I decided to apply.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t6">I would like to express my interest in the position of part-time bookshop assistant as advertised in The Post on Monday, 12th December.</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	<li>Which is the best way to refer to your CV?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t7">Read my CV for more details.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t8">You can check all this by looking at my CV.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t9">have a look at my CV and you'll see that ...</a></li>
	<li><a id="t10">As you can see from my CV, ...</a></li>
	<li><a id="t11">Please find enclosed my CV.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t12">Anyway, it's all in my CV so you can see for yourself.</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	<li>Which is the best way to refer to your experience?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t13">I've worked in loads of bookshops before.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t14">I have three years' experience in the retail industry.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t15">I have simply years of experience.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t16">I've got lots of experience in this business already.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t17">You'll be amazed at how experienced I am!</a></li>
	<li><a id="t18">I have considerable experience in sales.</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	<li>Which is the best way to express your availability for interview?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><a id="t19">I'm free all the time.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t20">I can come for an interview at a moment's notice.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t21">I can make it to an interview any time.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t22">Any time that suits you is fine by me.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t23">I am available for an interview at your convenience.</a></li>
	<li><a id="t24">I can have an interview whenever you like.</a></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	</ol>
